Boston Dynamics‚Äô ‚ÄòRobot Dog‚Äô May Be Available For Sale Soon #FACTS MAY. 13, 2018. #SpotMini the #doglike #robot that struck fear into the hearts of many when a #viralvideo showed it opening a door, is slated for commercial sale in the not-so-distant future

#MarcRaibert founder of the company #BostonDynamics which created the robots, made the announcement Friday at the #TechCrunch Sessions robotics conference at the #UniversityofCalifornia Berkeley. Raibert said the company intends to manufacture 100 SpotMinis this year as a ‚Äúprelude‚Äù to a ‚Äúhigher rate of production‚Äù in preparation for selling the product next year. He didn‚Äôt say how much the robot might cost

The SpotMini made headlines in February after Boston Dynamics published a video titled ‚ÄúHey Buddy, Can You Give Me a Hand?‚Äù The video shows one of the four-legged, yellow-and-black robots with an extendable claw opening a door to allow its companion, a fellow bot lacking the claw, to go through

The #video came just three months after a #WallStreetJournal article, headlined ‚ÄúHow to Survive a Robot Apocalypse: Just Close the Door,‚Äù noted that no robots in a government-sponsored contest had been able to open doors

Raibert said at the conference that the company designed SpotMini ‚Äúby thinking about what could go in an office ‚Äî in a space more accessible for business applications ‚Äî and then, the home eventually.‚Äù The robot can also navigate spaces autonomously, Wired notes. Basically, once a human operator #manually drives the robot around a particular area, the bot can create its own ‚Äúmap‚Äù and figure out how to walk over the same location on its own #NINFONETWORK #FOODNINFO #FOODNETWORK #BUZZFEED #NYC #LA #LONDON #ENEWS #WIRED #INSTAGOOD #FOXNEWS #CNN #FUTURISM #SPACEX #TESLA #BOSTON
